<p>

As the buildings have become taller and taller, rescue workers have to 
struggle with the need for devices to reach high in the tall buildings to help people in 
dangerous situations. While the self-extracting ladders have already shown their limitations, we have to look elsewhere for the solution. Rope climbing machines which can carry additional load (people and rescue equipment) to various heights in tall buildings have come up as possible solution.
<br><br>
In the Cliffhanger, we have tried to simplify the concept and bring that to students as a problem statement. We hope that the student community may find a novel solution 
to the problem that is faced by brave rescue workers everyday, who 
endanger their own lives to save others.<br><br>
