<p><strong><a name=grule><font color=#if3d55 size="1"><b>RULES OF THE GAME</b></font></a></strong><blockquote>
  <p>Although the spirit of this game is what matters, there are a few formal 
    restrictions. Below mentioned are some guidelines which every competitor should 
    follow. If a design does not fit these parameters or may but you are not sure, 
    please contact the organizers at the address mentioned below for clarifications.</p> 
  </p>
  <p><strong>Please note that any changes in these rules shall be intimated to 
    you by e-mails and indicated in <font color=red>red</font> on the website.</strong></p>
  <ol>
  <li> A maximum of three students per team is allowed. <br><br></li>
  <li>The machine should fit within (10x10x10) inch cube at any and every given 
    point of the game.<br><br></li>
  <li> The machine must use only mechanical power or mechanical power converted 
    from a source of electrical energy, chemicals, compressed gas, and rockets. 
    Pretensioned springs or combustion power method are strictly not allowed.<br><br></li>
  <li> Lift assisting devices like balloons are not permitted. Before starting, 
    the device must be demonstrated to be at full mechanical rest potential as 
    far as the structure will allow.<br><br></li>
  <li> The competitor will be allowed to engage the rope to his/her machine at 
    the beginning of the game. Youons are not allowed to touch your machine once 
    the game starts.<br><br></li>
  <li> The machine should climb up using only the rope and the support of the 
    wall.<br><br></li>
  <li> After reaching the terrace, the machine should completely disengage from 
    the rope before it starts bursting the balloons.<br><br></li>
  <li> Ten balloons will be arbitrarily placed inside each compartment. The machine 
    which bursts more number of balloons wins.<br><br></li>
  <li> Use of chemicals, fire or similar harmful things to burst the balloons 
    is prohibited.<br><br></li>
  <li> During the game if a balloon goes outside the board or in the opposite 
    compartment, it will be placed in its respective compartment by the judges 
    only.<br><br></li>
  <li> Duration of a game is 5 minutes. In case, one of the machine completes 
    its task (burst all the 10 balloons in its compartment) before time, the game 
    ends and that machine will be declared the winner.<br><br></li>
  <li>If both the machines fail to complete the given task within the time limit, 
    the machine which has burst a greater number of balloons will be declared 
    the winner. <br><br></li>
  <li>In case both machines fail to burst even one balloon after reaching the 
    top, the machine that reached the top first shall be declared the winner.<br><br></li>
  <li> In case both machines fail to reach the top, the machine which has climbed 
    more distance shall be declared the winner.<br><br></li>
  <li> If both machines have burst equal balloons or climbed an equal distance, 
    the game ends in a tie. In the case of a tie, the game will restart.<br><br></li>
  <li> If a machine gets stuck or falls down from the rope during the game, the 
    competitors are not allowed to touch it till the game is over. <br><br></li>
</ol>

<p>N.B. : The dimensions of the rope are always subject to slight errors. Please 
    keep room for minor modifications in your machine accordingly.<br>
</blockquote>
